						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">psycopathicteen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I don't think you need to worry that much about a CRT because most HDTVs support composite and component anyway.</div><br />Not well enough.  They'll upconvert (and deinterlace, even if it's supposed to be 240p) but the image quality is terrible, and more importantly the lag is really really bad.<br /><br />Last Christmas holiday, I played a game of Mario Golf with my brother, my sister, and my brother's wife.  I was the only one who picked a non-straight shooter (Mario, because he has one of the longest drives).  This screwed me when my mom decided to take a nap in the next room and we had to move upstairs and plug the N64 into an HDTV.  I couldn't hit the fairway to save my life; the timing was off by at least a tenth of the swing bar.  My brother ended up beating me with Plum.<br /><br />If we'd been playing Duck Hunt we'd have had to quit.</div>

